annotationA: Alpha-(1,6)-fucosyltransferase; Catalyzes the addition of fucose in alpha 1-6 linkage to the first GlcNAc residue, next to the peptide chains in N-glycans. The addition is prevented if the GlcNAc residue is already fucosylated
annotationB: Fucosyltransferase activity; alpha-(1->3)-fucosyltransferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: protein glycosylation; Belongs to the glycosyltransferase 10 family
